8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Galileo AI and Uizard share a solid foundation of core features including Ai Generation, Export Formats, Responsive. On the other hand, Uizard uniquely offers Templates and Drag And Drop and Brand Kit and Collaboration and Stock Assets, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Galileo AI holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Uizard scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Uizard comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Galileo AI begins at $19/mo. Uizard stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Galileo AI requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
